1
00:00:06,131 --> 00:00:09,176
<i>["Headhunt" by Okamoto's]</i>

2
00:00:09,176 --> 00:00:12,262
[man singing in Japanese]

3
00:00:12,262 --> 00:00:19,269
<i>♪ ♪</i>

4
00:01:01,687 --> 00:01:02,896
KYOHEI: Who's Hollywood?

5
00:01:02,896 --> 00:01:04,356
ERIKA:
And then they say

6
00:01:04,356 --> 00:01:06,108
he strips every shred of flesh
off his victims

7
00:01:06,108 --> 00:01:07,526
so there's nothing left
but the bone.

8
00:01:07,526 --> 00:01:08,527
KURURI: What's that?

9
00:01:08,527 --> 00:01:09,653
SHIZUO: Somewhere near here,

10
00:01:09,653 --> 00:01:11,446
there's a sushi restaurant.

11
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:14,575
‐ This shadow cocoon thing‐‐
I can't seem to break out of it.

12
00:01:14,575 --> 00:01:16,702
‐ I'm a monster, but so what?

13
00:01:16,702 --> 00:01:17,953
Who gives a damn?

14
00:01:17,953 --> 00:01:20,998
I don't care anymore!

15
00:01:20,998 --> 00:01:24,084
[man singing in Japanese]

16
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:31,091
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17
00:01:56,658 --> 00:01:58,243
RURI:
Why in the world did I end up

18
00:01:58,243 --> 00:02:00,954
becoming
a bloodthirsty murderer?

19
00:02:00,954 --> 00:02:02,998
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20
00:02:02,998 --> 00:02:04,708
And why in the world

21
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:07,210
did I end up becoming a monster?

22
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:10,756
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23
00:02:10,756 --> 00:02:12,257
It makes me nauseous.

24
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:16,178
I feel sick
every time I kill them.

25
00:02:16,178 --> 00:02:18,180
No.
No. No.

26
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:19,222
This isn't right.

27
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:21,141
I can't let anyone love me.

28
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,934
I've got to become a monster‐‐

29
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:25,312
a monster no one understands.

30
00:02:25,312 --> 00:02:27,564
And then they'll finally pay.

31
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:28,940
No. Not them.

32
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:32,277
Just the one.
I'm gonna kill him.

33
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:35,906
Him? Who?
Answer me.

34
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:39,284
Who? Where?
No! I don't want this!

35
00:02:39,284 --> 00:02:41,495
Mom! Where are you?

36
00:02:41,495 --> 00:02:44,122
Please save me. Save me.

37
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:48,460
SHIZUO: Bastards.

38
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:50,462
You're
a bunch of damn petty thieves!

39
00:02:50,462 --> 00:02:52,089
‐ Shizuo.

40
00:02:53,465 --> 00:02:56,593
MAN: In that moment,
the past reawakened

41
00:02:56,593 --> 00:03:00,430
and flashed across the mind
of the serial killer Hollywood.

42
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:03,684
The monsters
she admired since childhood

43
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:05,435
doing as they pleased,

44
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:09,815
living their lives
without considering others.

45
00:03:09,815 --> 00:03:13,110
Born into one of the wealthiest
families in the area,

46
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:16,780
she was forced to constantly
play the role of a blue blood.

47
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:18,448
‐ Huh?

48
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:20,784
MAN: That house is gone now.

49
00:03:20,784 --> 00:03:24,746
Losing her family, fortune,
and all sense of honor,

50
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,706
in exchange,
she gained her freedom

51
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:27,958
for the first time.

52
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:29,334
RURI: In the end,

53
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:31,878
I got to meet a real monster.

54
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:33,588
Not a fake one like me,

55
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:36,925
but a genuine monster
with overwhelming power.

56
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:19,551
‐ This is fascinating.

57
00:04:19,551 --> 00:04:21,344
She heals faster than anybody

58
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:23,305
outside of
Celty and your brother.

59
00:04:23,305 --> 00:04:25,432
It's honestly
a little hard to believe.

60
00:04:25,432 --> 00:04:27,225
Her life's not in danger.

61
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:29,394
She might even be walking soon.

62
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:31,521
‐ Thanks for doing this.
‐ Sure thing.

63
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:34,065
It's not like I can turn down
Shizuo's little brother.

64
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:36,067
Getting punched
all the way to Mars for refusing

65
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:37,569
isn't high on my bucket list.

66
00:04:37,569 --> 00:04:39,237
YUHEI:
Sorry he's always troubling you.

67
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:41,239
‐ [laughs]
He looks out for Celty,

68
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:44,576
so I'm actually more grateful
than anything.

69
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:46,203
Hey, could I have some water?

70
00:04:46,203 --> 00:04:47,537
I'm kind of thirsty.

71
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:51,082
YUHEI: Yeah, sure.
SHINRA: Thanks.

72
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:53,084
[Dokusonmaru meows]

73
00:04:53,084 --> 00:04:56,087
SHINRA: Oh, she's awake.

74
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:57,798
Are you all right?

75
00:04:57,798 --> 00:05:00,842
Probably just feels like
a dull ache, right?

76
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:05,013
I have to admit,
I'm a little geeked out.

77
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:06,389
Considering my line of work,

78
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:08,558
I never thought
I'd ever meet someone like you.

79
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:12,312
It's really an honor,
Ms. Hijiribe.

80
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:13,814
MAN: Ruri Hijiribe.

81
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:16,149
Born September the 27th.

82
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:17,984
Age unknown.

83
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:20,570
She's a popular idol
whose pale skin

84
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:22,614
and somewhat gloomy
yet attractive looks

85
00:05:22,614 --> 00:05:25,492
give her an allure
that seems otherworldly.

86
00:05:25,492 --> 00:05:27,869
She started as a makeup artist,

87
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:30,497
apprentice to Tenjin Zakuroya.

88
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:32,874
Her work on
"Vampire Ninja: Carmilla Saizou"

89
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:35,001
was critically acclaimed,
and she's rated

90
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,628
in the top 100 makeup artists

91
00:05:36,628 --> 00:05:38,922
by the World Film Federation.

92
00:05:38,922 --> 00:05:42,634
Later, she was scouted by
the Yodogiri Shining Corporation

93
00:05:42,634 --> 00:05:44,386
and made her debut as a model.

94
00:05:44,386 --> 00:05:47,264
She's been on a roll ever since.

95
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:50,725
‐ Hey, stop that, Dokusonmaru.

96
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:52,644
‐ Dokusonmaru?

97
00:05:52,644 --> 00:05:54,813
‐ His full name
is Yuigadokusonmaru.

98
00:05:54,813 --> 00:05:56,356
Cute, right?

99
00:05:56,356 --> 00:05:57,649
‐ You ought to
give smiling a try

100
00:05:57,649 --> 00:05:58,942
when you're holding a cat.

101
00:05:58,942 --> 00:06:00,569
‐ Huh?
‐ It's kind of unnerving.

102
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:01,862
‐ I am smiling.

103
00:06:01,862 --> 00:06:03,488
‐ [laughs]

104
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:06,491
If he ever met you, my dad
would want to dissect you.

105
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:07,492
[cell phone ringing]

106
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:09,786
Oh, I should take this.

107
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:11,705
‐ Yuhei Hanejima.

108
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:13,498
Is that you?

109
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:15,000
‐ Thank goodness.

110
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,003
You look better than I thought.

111
00:06:18,003 --> 00:06:20,130
Water? You look thirsty.

112
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:23,133
<i>[string music]</i>

113
00:06:23,133 --> 00:06:27,345
<i>♪ ♪</i>

114
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:30,223
‐ Sorry.
It's another urgent case.

115
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,683
What lousy timing.

116
00:06:31,683 --> 00:06:34,436
How often do you get the chance
to meet Ruri Hijiribe?

117
00:06:34,436 --> 00:06:37,480
‐ Thank you for coming out
in the middle of the night.

118
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,523
‐ My pleasure.

119
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:39,858
If you really want to thank me,

120
00:06:39,858 --> 00:06:41,359
could you get me her autograph?

121
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:43,987
And one for Celty too, okay?

122
00:06:43,987 --> 00:06:46,364
‐ I'll do my best.
‐ That's all I ask!

123
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:48,366
And I won't charge you
for this house call.

124
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:50,869
‐ Hold on. I can't‐‐
‐ Don't worry about it.

125
00:06:50,869 --> 00:06:52,704
I'm planning
on gouging my next patient

126
00:06:52,704 --> 00:06:54,372
for ruining this for me anyway.

127
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:56,333
Give my best to Shizuo, okay?

128
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,834
I'll show myself out.

129
00:06:57,834 --> 00:06:59,544
[Dokusonmaru growls]

130
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:01,880
[door opens, shuts]

131
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:04,090
RURI:
What exactly am I doing here?

132
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:07,093
‐ You fell out of nowhere
right in front of my car.

133
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:08,470
I wasn't quite sure what to do,

134
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:10,513
so I brought you here
and called a doctor

135
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:12,057
to take a look at you.

136
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:14,059
‐ Why bring me here
and not a hospital?

137
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:16,936
‐ There are several reasons
I can think of.

138
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:18,605
Mainly,
I thought that a hospital

139
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:19,898
would be a problem for you.

140
00:07:19,898 --> 00:07:21,399
‐ Huh?

141
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:25,236
YUHEI: May I ask you something?
‐ What is it?

142
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:28,406
‐ The serial killer they call
"Hollywood" in the news.

143
00:07:28,406 --> 00:07:31,076
That's you, isn't it?

144
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:33,036
‐ Damn it.
What are you thinking,

145
00:07:33,036 --> 00:07:35,246
bringing that injured
pain in the ass here?

146
00:07:35,246 --> 00:07:36,790
SHINRA: That'll be 200,000 yen.

147
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,500
‐ [gasps]
You serious?

148
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,960
‐ I don't come cheap,
especially when your emergency

149
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,212
dragged me away from a chance

150
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:44,130
to spend time
with Ruri Hijiribe.

151
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,757
‐ Come on, two of you.

152
00:07:45,757 --> 00:07:47,342
Fighting no good.

153
00:07:47,342 --> 00:07:50,595
You must do
the "pain, pain, go away"

154
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:53,056
on Egor's injuries, doctor.

155
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:55,809
I beg you, please.
I'm 100% okay, all right?

156
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:57,310
SHINRA: Fine, I'll do my best.

157
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,479
Just get the money ready, okay?

158
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:00,605
By the way,

159
00:08:00,605 --> 00:08:02,440
Egor is the patient's name,
right?

160
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:03,441
‐ Yeah, that's right.

161
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:04,859
We were in the same organization

162
00:08:04,859 --> 00:08:06,069
back home in Russia.

163
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:08,738
But who the hell cares anymore?

164
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:10,115
‐ Oh! He picked up.

165
00:08:10,115 --> 00:08:11,866
Izaya, it's Mairu.

166
00:08:11,866 --> 00:08:13,243
‐ Yeah, what do you want?

167
00:08:13,243 --> 00:08:14,869
Make it short.
I'm busy, okay?

168
00:08:14,869 --> 00:08:16,871
MAIRU:
Does the name Celty Sturluson

169
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:18,248
ring any bells for you?

170
00:08:18,248 --> 00:08:21,292
‐ Heh. Celty?
Yeah, I might know something.

171
00:08:21,292 --> 00:08:22,460
Why do you ask?

172
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,379
MAIRU: What do you know
about this person?

173
00:08:24,379 --> 00:08:25,588
IZAYA: Hmm.

174
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:27,298
I know
it has nothing to do with you.

175
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:28,800
‐ You do know something,
don't you?

176
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,760
I knew it!
Why won't you tell?

177
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:33,096
That's not fair!
That's not fair!

178
00:08:33,096 --> 00:08:34,097
[line clicks]

179
00:08:34,097 --> 00:08:35,348
‐ What did he say?

180
00:08:35,348 --> 00:08:36,599
‐ [growls]
Jeez!

181
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:38,268
I can't believe
he just did that!

182
00:08:38,268 --> 00:08:39,602
He hung up on me!

183
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:41,396
So that's not gonna work.

184
00:08:41,396 --> 00:08:42,814
Okay, let's see.

185
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:44,357
‐ I wish
I could turn my cell off

186
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:45,650
and ignore those two,

187
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:48,778
but I've got a business to run
here.

188
00:08:50,155 --> 00:08:52,157
<i>♪ ♪</i>

189
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:55,702
‐ [grunting]

190
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:57,829
Shingen?

191
00:08:57,829 --> 00:08:59,831
Oh. I'm sorry.

192
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:02,917
I mistook you for someone else.

193
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:04,002
‐ Hmm.

194
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:07,505
MAIRU: Hey there.
Feeling better?

195
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:08,757
‐ Are you all right, mister?

196
00:09:08,757 --> 00:09:10,216
‐ I'm sure he'll be fine.

197
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,677
And plastic surgery
can do wonders these days.

198
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:15,638
Besides, you look kind of cool
bandaged up like that.

199
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:17,182
‐ Young ladies.

200
00:09:17,182 --> 00:09:19,809
I haven't had the chance
to thank you for what you did.

201
00:09:19,809 --> 00:09:20,935
I appreciate it.

202
00:09:20,935 --> 00:09:22,145
‐ It's 200 large.

203
00:09:22,145 --> 00:09:24,147
Come on, Egor.
Pay the doc.

204
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:26,191
‐ I'm afraid
I don't have any money.

205
00:09:26,191 --> 00:09:29,027
It's unfortunate, but
I mishandled the job earlier.

206
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:31,154
The fact
that I didn't ask for an advance

207
00:09:31,154 --> 00:09:32,739
is something I now regret.

208
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:34,282
‐ I'd like to put it up for you,

209
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:35,909
but we have to get stock
for tomorrow‐‐

210
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:37,202
‐ Stock day already?

211
00:09:37,202 --> 00:09:39,120
Why not take day off instead?

212
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,872
We can make it holiday.

213
00:09:40,872 --> 00:09:43,792
National Sushi Day‐‐
‐ Shut up, and get back to work.

214
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:47,712
‐ Hey, Mister.

215
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:49,714
‐ Huh?
‐ The money.

216
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:51,925
Want us to cover it for you?

217
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:54,886
‐ If that's what you suspected,

218
00:09:54,886 --> 00:09:58,098
why didn't you turn me in
to the police?

219
00:09:58,098 --> 00:10:01,184
‐ Did you want me
to turn you in?

220
00:10:01,184 --> 00:10:04,187
If so,
you should've done it yourself.

221
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:09,818
‐ When you took me in,

222
00:10:09,818 --> 00:10:12,904
didn't you think
I might attack you?

223
00:10:12,904 --> 00:10:14,781
I'm gonna be blunt about this.

224
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:16,574
The way you're acting right now,

225
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:19,869
it's obvious that you're not
putting on some kind of act,

226
00:10:19,869 --> 00:10:22,247
but to be honest, you're crazy.

227
00:10:22,247 --> 00:10:24,874
‐ You really think so?
‐ I do.

228
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:27,418
Letting a murderer
come inside your home.

229
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:29,254
It's insane.

230
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:30,463
There was a very good chance

231
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:32,799
that doing this
would get you killed.

232
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:35,093
Did you ever stop
to consider that fact?

233
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:43,059
‐ So,
don't you think it's about time

234
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:44,602
you explained yourself, Dad?

235
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:47,105
‐ Uh, you see,
Egor's kind of what you'd call

236
00:10:47,105 --> 00:10:48,773
a jack‐of‐all‐trades.

237
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:52,402
I hired him
to apprehend a certain woman.

238
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:54,487
‐ A woman?
‐ Right.

239
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:57,031
Do you know about
that serial killer, Hollywood?

240
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:59,868
Well, after investigating
that incident at Nebula,

241
00:10:59,868 --> 00:11:02,287
I stumbled across a woman
whose ancestors had

242
00:11:02,287 --> 00:11:04,247
an interesting
genetic abnormality.

243
00:11:04,247 --> 00:11:07,625
Rather than let her be arrested
and given the death sentence,

244
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:09,752
I thought we could take her in,
dissect her,

245
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:12,297
pump her full of her drugs,
have a good time‐‐

246
00:11:12,297 --> 00:11:13,923
you know, the usual thing.

247
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:14,966
What do you think?

248
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:16,384
‐ I'm not so sure, Dad.

249
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:18,428
How about you show
a little restraint for once?

250
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:21,014
SHINGEN: I'm surprised to hear
that from you of all people.

251
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:22,390
Whatever.

252
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:24,851
I hear she got clobbered
by someone on the street,

253
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:26,394
so how impressive could she be?

254
00:11:26,394 --> 00:11:28,813
It didn't sound like
much of a specimen.

255
00:11:28,813 --> 00:11:30,815
You may as well ignore this.

256
00:11:30,815 --> 00:11:33,193
‐ Say, Dad.
This woman of yours.

257
